# DiffusionSystem

## Purpose
Drives in-engine text-to-image generation (ADR 0008). Returns early until the engine config and
resource map exist. Lazily creates the diffusion backend + job singletons (deferred), then loads the
resident checkpoint (+ optional ControlNet) once from the resource map's model paths. Each frame it
reaps a finished Diffusion Job — emitting a RegisterGeneratedTextureRequest carrying the result — and,
while idle and the backend is loaded, assembles one GenerateImageRequest into backend job parameters
(resolving Generation Config defaults, LoRA UUIDs to paths, and the OpenPose Control Hint by rasterizing
the referenced skeleton) and launches a single generation on a background worker thread so the frame
loop never blocks. Only one job runs at a time.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| GenerateImageRequestOneFrameComponent | read | App-emitted request: prompt, overrides, LoRA refs, optional OpenPose ControlNet, target UUID |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | Resident checkpoint/ControlNet paths, LoRA paths, OpenPose skeletons |
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | Generation Config defaults for unset request fields |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| DiffusionBackendSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once (holds the platform backend); m_LoadAttempted guards the one-time checkpoint load |
| DiffusionJobSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Holds the single active/just-finished job (worker thread + atomic state + result) |
| RegisterGeneratedTextureRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Emitted when a job completes; drained by ResourceManagerSystem |
